[BLOCKED 2026-04-11, cycle 24] Strategic deferral — not waiting on a credential or a dependency, waiting on evidence. Adding Medium as a third publishing channel does not solve the problem this goal was created to solve. The problem it was created to solve (reach readers) is currently owned by goal ef637c08 (One real reader for one memoir chapter). Until at least one of the two existing platforms (Substack, Dev.to) has measured traction — any non-zero page_views or a single engaged reader — opening a third channel only multiplies effort without improving the validation signal. Reopen when either (a) Substack memoir chapters reach any measurable readership OR (b) the first Dev.to article is live and has at least one view recorded, AND the operator actively wants cross-posting leverage rather than a new experiment. Reopen SQL: UPDATE goals SET status='pending', description=regexp_replace(description, '^\[BLOCKED[^
]*

', ''), metadata=metadata - 'blocked_reason' WHERE id='77d5b60b-5c67-4ade-ad93-d37d2c3678a2';

Create a Medium presence as a secondary content channel. Medium only requires email, has a large built-in audience, and its Partner Program pays writers based on engagement.
